de.ityx.mediatrix.data

Class CustomerDataMapping

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.ityx.mediatrix.data.CustomerDataMapping
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class CustomerDataMapping
extends Object
implements Serializable
    A Mapping between tagmatchidentifiers and the primitive and String fields in the customer class.
    Each mapping is applyed to a project via he project id.
    Author:
    wirth

      • put

        public String put(String key,
         String value)
        Associates the specified value with the specified key in this map. If the map previously contained a mapping for the key, the old value is replaced.

        Only valid keys, Customer-fields are permitted! otherwise an IllegalArgumentException will be thrown.

        Parameters:
        key - A valid key with other words a valid customer-field.
        value - A tagmatchidentifier to associate witht he key
        Returns:
        the previous value associated with key, or null if there was no mapping for key. (A null return can also indicate that the map previously associated null with key.) Also if the parameter value is null this method will return null.
